=E2=84=B9=EF=B8=8F About DAS

DAS 2022 is the 15th edition of the IAPR sponsored workshop focusing on sys=
tem-level issues and approaches for document analysis and recognition. The =
workshop consists of invited keynote speeches, oral and poster paper presen=
tations, tutorials, and working group discussions.

Accepted Papers.  The accepted papers at DAS 2022 cover a wide range of top=
ics, including Image Processing, OCR, HTR, Forensics, Historical Document A=
nalysis, Natural Language Processing, Information Retrieval, Deep Learning,=
 and Datasets and Evaluation.

A Quick Summary of Paper Submissions and Acceptances:
* 88 full-length papers were submitted for DAS 2022=20
  - 31 were accepted for an oral presentation, and
  - 21 for a poster presentation.=20
* 16 short papers were also submitted to DAS 2022, and accepted for poster =
presentation.


=F0=9F=8F=96=EF=B8=8F Location

DAS 2022 will be hosted by La Rochelle University (France) on May 22-25, 20=
22. The city of La Rochelle, situated on the central west coast of France, =
possesses a rich historical fabric including the Saint-Nicolas tower and ur=
ban heritage. In the early 21st century, the city has consistently been ran=
ked among France=E2=80=99s most liveable cities.=20


=F0=9F=8E=A4 Keynotes and Tutorials

* Keynote 1: =E2=80=9CAutomatic Question Answering & Generation in News Arc=
hives=E2=80=9D by Professor Adam Jatowt (University of Innsbruck, Austria)

* Keynote 2: =E2=80=9CThe kiss of the Prince=E2=80=9D: Bringing Document Co=
ntent to Life by Professor Andreas Dengel (German Research Center for Artif=
icial Intelligence (DFKI) in Kaiserslautern, Germany)

* Tutorial: =E2=80=9CUnlocking the Potential of Unstructured Data in Financ=
e Through Document Intelligence=E2=80=9D by Himanshu Sharad Bhatt (Research=
 Director at American Express AI Labs, India)


